{% else -%}
This stage projects the capital-income facts classified under [§ 20 Abs. 1 / Abs. 2 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__20.html) onto the individual Zeilen of Anlage KAP / KAP-INV. Inputs come from the typed sale and income facts (``de.capital.sale_facts`` / ``de.capital.income_facts``), the InvStG § 20 fund classification (``de.capital.fund_classification``), the Shareworks equity-comp sidecar (``de.capital.dher_stock_gain``), and the gross 1099 foreign-tax amount (``de.kap.foreign_tax_1099_eur``). The stage replaces the prior script-level arithmetic at ``germany_projections.py:113`` with a fingerprinted rule so every rendered Zeile traces to a ``StageResult.output_fingerprint`` (invariants I2 / I5 in ``docs/invariant-migration-plan.md``).

The JStG 2024 (Empfehlung Nr. 4a des Finanzausschusses, in force 06.12.2024) deleted [§ 20 Abs. 6 Sätze 5 und 6 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__20.html) without replacement. The former 2024 Vordruck lines for Termingeschäft positives, Termingeschäft losses, and Uneinbringlichkeit von Kapitalforderungen are therefore dropped for VZ 2025; their economic effect flows entirely through the surviving [§ 20 Abs. 6 Sätze 1–4 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__20.html) netting and lands in the Zeile-19 sum. The Aktien-specific loss-netting under Satz 4 is unchanged.

Inputs:

- **1099 gross foreign tax (Anlage KAP Zeile 41)**: **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["de.kap.foreign_tax_1099_eur"].value | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- **DHER equity-comp stock gain** ([§ 19a EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__19a.html) → [§ 20 Abs. 2 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__20.html)): **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["de.capital.dher_stock_gain"].value | money(currency="EUR") }}**

